<h2> III.  PRIORITY OF OBSERVATIONS IN ASTRONOMY</h2>

 Astronomy is driven more by <u>new observational discoveries</u> than
       by fundamental interpretive insights (i.e. theory).  The
       development of astrophysics has been shaped by observations in
       about 3/4 of the instances.</p>

